01:10:09.456 --> 01:10:13.176
tumors as well. When cGAS is up in micronuclei,

1206
01:10:13.376 --> 01:10:15.536
STING levels are low in cancer cells.

1207
01:10:15.606 --> 01:10:19.556
And they're low because it's being activated and degraded, not because

1208
01:10:19.576 --> 01:10:22.876
it's inactive. So it's actually chronic activation. So cGAS high, STING low.

1209
01:10:23.476 --> 01:10:27.016
And the other way around, when cGAS is not on micronuclei,

1210
01:10:27.456 --> 01:10:30.316
we see very high levels of STING in cancer cells.

1211
01:10:30.356 --> 01:10:34.276
The stroma is always highly expressing because the stroma doesn't have micronuclei.

1212
01:10:34.736 --> 01:10:38.556
So we basically asked whether the cGAS high, STING low, cGAS low, STING high

1213
01:10:39.056 --> 01:10:42.736
in pre-treatment samples could predict response to STING agonists.

1214
01:10:42.776 --> 01:10:46.096
Of course, it's very hard to get sufficient samples homogenized in

1215
01:10:46.136 --> 01:10:49.936
the same cancer type in these dose escalation studies, so we have

1216
01:10:49.976 --> 01:10:52.596
to contend with a small number here.

1217
01:10:52.616 --> 01:10:56.216
But in these 12 patients, we did see that the responders tended to

1218
01:10:56.256 --> 01:10:59.936
have low levels of cGAS-positive micronuclei and high

1219
01:11:00.016 --> 01:11:03.556
levels of STING, and the inverse was also true.

1220
01:11:03.896 --> 01:11:07.386
Patients that had high levels of cGAS and low levels of STING did not

1221
01:11:07.396 --> 01:11:11.156
respond. So at least this could potentially be developed

1222
01:11:11.196 --> 01:11:11.856
further into a

1223
01:11:13.256 --> 01:11:14.616
patient selection biomarker.

1224
01:11:15.716 --> 01:11:19.656
And obviously the dream is to basically therapeutically intervene

1225
01:11:20.036 --> 01:11:23.916
by inhibiting cGAS to allow everybody to basically

1226
01:11:23.936 --> 01:11:25.456
respond to these STING agonists or

1227
01:11:26.316 --> 01:11:28.876
more patients to respond to it than they currently do.

1228
01:11:29.796 --> 01:11:32.396
So this is kind of the summary of the first part of the talk,

1229
01:11:33.696 --> 01:11:37.576
where basically this pathway has the potential to

1230
01:11:37.616 --> 01:11:40.236
be a strong therapeutic

1231
01:11:41.136 --> 01:11:44.436
target or STING in particular. But we need to do it at the right

1232
01:11:44.896 --> 01:11:48.426
cadence, at the right time, and the right context, which is the acute activation,

1233
01:11:48.816 --> 01:11:52.756
and this gives you the anti-tumor response, high levels of interferon response.

1234
01:11:54.156 --> 01:11:57.256
Once it's allowed to chronically activate, as in with

1235
01:11:57.536 --> 01:12:01.516
cGAMP production because of chromosomal instability, it gives you

1236
01:12:01.556 --> 01:12:05.216
this ER stress response, and it becomes basically

1237
01:12:05.256 --> 01:12:08.616
non-responsive to further STING agonism.

1238
01:12:08.976 --> 01:12:12.736
It's no surprise if you give a patient PARP inhibitors sub-therapeutically for

1239
01:12:12.816 --> 01:12:16.692
five yearsor any drug for that matter,

1240
01:12:16.772 --> 01:12:19.852
there's a very high likelihood that five years later, they may not respond to a

1241
01:12:19.892 --> 01:12:23.182
therapeutic dose because the tumor figures a way out of it, and this actually just

1242
01:12:23.212 --> 01:12:24.132
takes five days.

1243
01:12:26.132 --> 01:12:28.752
But we're lucky in that it's reversible.

1244
01:12:29.732 --> 01:12:33.452
Okay, so with that part of the talk, I'm going to switch back to the cell

1245
01:12:33.552 --> 01:12:34.352
intrinsic

1246
01:12:35.152 --> 01:12:39.092
consequences of chromosomal instability, and a theme that you heard earlier

1247
01:12:39.132 --> 01:12:42.812
in Uri's talk is KIF18A and KIF18A inhibitors.

1248
01:12:42.872 --> 01:12:45.692
So in 2021, KIF18A

1249
01:12:46.632 --> 01:12:50.072
became this really interesting target in chromosomal instability

1250
01:12:50.632 --> 01:12:51.752
and led to

1251
01:12:53.592 --> 01:12:57.021
quite a bit of effort to develop inhibitors to KIF18A.

1252
01:12:57.072 --> 01:13:00.892
It's a kinesin protein that walks on microtubules, and it's important in

1253
01:13:00.952 --> 01:13:03.032
satisfying the spindle assembly checkpoint.

1254
01:13:04.582 --> 01:13:07.972
And when KIF18A is inhibited, normal cells divide fine.

1255
01:13:08.912 --> 01:13:11.632
T cells can divide, normal epithelial cells can divide.

1256
01:13:12.052 --> 01:13:15.472
So it's actually a cancer selective antimitotic agent.

1257
01:13:16.372 --> 01:13:20.222
What was clear, however, in clinical development is that

1258
01:13:20.252 --> 01:13:24.242
KIF18A inhibition doesn't work in every

1259
01:13:24.242 --> 01:13:28.032
chromosomally unstable tumor. So it was clear that while chromosomal

1260
01:13:28.042 --> 01:13:31.212
instability, aneuploidy, and whole genome doubling are

1261
01:13:31.272 --> 01:13:35.072
necessary for the synthetic lethal, they're not sufficient.

1262
01:13:35.132 --> 01:13:36.012
In other words, there's

1263
01:13:37.052 --> 01:13:41.012
a subset of chromosomally unstable tumors that

1264
01:13:41.072 --> 01:13:43.692
likely will respond, not every tumor type.

1265
01:13:44.132 --> 01:13:47.572
So through a concerted effort to identify a biomarker for

1266
01:13:47.692 --> 01:13:51.632
KIF18A response, and actually in addition, a mechanism of response, we

1267
01:13:51.692 --> 01:13:55.332
focused on the spindle assembly checkpoint, which as Uri mentioned, is really

1268
01:13:55.352 --> 01:13:57.762
the way by which KIF18A makes cells

1269
01:13:57.812 --> 01:14:00.862
sensitive to inhibition.

1270
01:14:01.352 --> 01:14:05.072
So spindle assembly checkpoint is a complex signaling cascade that

1271
01:14:05.132 --> 01:14:05.792
ultimately

1272
01:14:06.692 --> 01:14:10.272
is distilled in a protein called MAD2 that goes to the

1273
01:14:10.312 --> 01:14:13.912
kinetochores, which are the attachment sites of chromosomes to microtubules.

1274
01:14:14.272 --> 01:14:18.112
And it basically is signaling and forces the cells to wait

1275
01:14:18.332 --> 01:14:22.292
until all the chromosomes have aligned, and boom, once they've all

1276
01:14:22.312 --> 01:14:26.052
aligned, MAD2 falls off and anaphase can happen.

1277
01:14:27.592 --> 01:14:31.532
If you knock out KIF18A, cells kind of remain in mitosis for a long

1278
01:14:31.572 --> 01:14:35.472
time. MAD2 remains active and cells die because they

1279
01:14:35.512 --> 01:14:38.672
can't arrest the mitosis for more than a couple of hours and survive.

1280
01:14:38.772 --> 01:14:42.392
So once cells arrest the mitosis for more than a couple of hours, they either die

1281
01:14:42.432 --> 01:14:44.792
during mitosis or as soon as they exit.

1282
01:14:45.592 --> 01:14:46.532
But not every cell

1283
01:14:47.452 --> 01:14:50.692
line would arrest in response to KIF18A inhibition.

1284
01:14:51.172 --> 01:14:54.852
So we started looking at regulators of the spindle assembly

1285
01:14:54.912 --> 01:14:57.512
checkpoint signaling, and actually zeroed in on RB,

1286
01:14:58.492 --> 01:15:02.372
because it turns out from old literature in 2003, and

1287
01:15:02.412 --> 01:15:02.822
I'm sorry

1288
01:15:03.772 --> 01:15:06.472
I should have had the citation here, Hernandez et al in Nature

1289
01:15:06.652 --> 01:15:10.612
2003. It turns out that E2F is actually a

1290
01:15:10.732 --> 01:15:14.072
key regulator of MAD2, and E2F

1291
01:15:14.092 --> 01:15:16.532
directly leads to the transcription of MAD2.

1292
01:15:17.212 --> 01:15:17.432
So

1293
01:15:18.252 --> 01:15:21.812
if RB is activated, E2F is restrained, and

1294
01:15:21.852 --> 01:15:24.812
MAD2 levels are probably within the normal range.

1295
01:15:25.352 --> 01:15:27.692
However, when RB is lost,

1296
01:15:28.752 --> 01:15:32.082
E2F goes up, activity goes up, and you make a lot of

1297
01:15:32.132 --> 01:15:35.692
MAD2, and this is probably the substrate that

1298
01:15:36.212 --> 01:15:40.112
KIF18A inhibitors need in order to arrest the cells

1299
01:15:40.152 --> 01:15:42.152
and impart their therapeutic effect.

1300
01:15:42.872 --> 01:15:46.612
And in addition, E2F is also a

1301
01:15:46.672 --> 01:15:50.032
transcription factor for CDKN2A or p16.

1302
01:15:50.952 --> 01:15:54.832
So in one way, MAD2 levels are up. This is what

1303
01:15:54.912 --> 01:15:58.452
you need for KIF18A inhibition. But also you're getting

1304
01:15:58.532 --> 01:16:02.312
p16, which is a protein that's widely used in the clinic in head and neck

1305
01:16:02.332 --> 01:16:06.032
cancers and cervical cancers to identify HPV associated

1306
01:16:06.072 --> 01:16:09.852
tumors. And why is it used there? Because HPV basically

1307
01:16:09.872 --> 01:16:13.492
knocks out RB through E6 and E7, and so

1308
01:16:13.552 --> 01:16:17.012
p16 is a marker for RB pathway inactivation.

1309
01:16:17.452 --> 01:16:21.292
And the reason it's a marker for RB pathway inactivation is because E2F is trying

1310
01:16:21.302 --> 01:16:25.292
to reactivate RB through p16, but if RB is genomically lost

1311
01:16:25.832 --> 01:16:29.532
or if it's hyperphosphorylated from cyclin E and CDK2,

1312
01:16:29.992 --> 01:16:30.992
you get very little--

1313
01:16:32.072 --> 01:16:35.761
p16 alone cannot restore RB function,

1314
01:16:35.812 --> 01:16:37.432
basically. But it's a really good biomarker.

1315
01:16:38.392 --> 01:16:42.212
So we tested this hypothesis pre-clinically in three different

1316
01:16:42.612 --> 01:16:46.092
cell line panels using different KIF18A inhibitors.

1317
01:16:46.412 --> 01:16:49.232
This study was not done with the purpose of looking for RB.

1318
01:16:50.212 --> 01:16:52.712
This was a breadth of efficacy study with various inhibitors

1319
01:16:53.792 --> 01:16:56.712
in a large panel of close to 1,000 cell lines.

1320
01:16:57.312 --> 01:17:00.752
And basically what we find is the cells that we know have

1321
01:17:00.812 --> 01:17:04.492
alterations in the RB pathway tend to be more sensitive in each of

1322
01:17:04.572 --> 01:17:08.032
these than the ones that don't have alterations in the RB pathway.

1323
01:17:08.092 --> 01:17:11.432
And this was recently deposited in a preprint as well.

