1459
01:25:13.184 --> 01:25:16.644
Yeah. Excellent question. And of course, the biology is always a little bit more

1460
01:25:16.684 --> 01:25:17.284
complicated.

1461
01:25:18.564 --> 01:25:22.484
So there's a part that I didn't talk about, the study that we did, as you may

1462
01:25:22.584 --> 01:25:26.124
be aware, is EMPP1, which is an extracellular hydrolase,

1463
01:25:26.764 --> 01:25:29.504
that when cancer cells are producing cGAMP,

1464
01:25:30.544 --> 01:25:34.264
they pump it outside of the cell into the microenvironment, and that's broken up by

1465
01:25:34.284 --> 01:25:38.204
EMPP1 into AMP, and then CD73 or NT5E breaks

1466
01:25:38.244 --> 01:25:41.684
that down into adenosine. And adenosine, as you know, is a strong immune

1467
01:25:41.704 --> 01:25:45.044
suppressor. So it's not that STING is not

1468
01:25:45.264 --> 01:25:48.164
needed in the host. You need it, ideally.

1469
01:25:48.684 --> 01:25:52.384
But if you're getting M2 macrophages, they're not going to respond or-- I'm sorry,

1470
01:25:52.904 --> 01:25:55.104
M2 like, how are immune suppressive macros--

1471
01:25:56.124 --> 01:25:59.984
Basically, if you have an immune suppressive TME, it will not respond as well to

1472
01:26:00.024 --> 01:26:02.424
STING agonist as if you have it more primed.

1473
01:26:02.964 --> 01:26:05.844
So I think it actually might explain that.

1474
01:26:05.864 --> 01:26:09.424
And actually, one of the interesting thing is in early stage

1475
01:26:10.644 --> 01:26:12.424
tumor formation, there is a

1476
01:26:13.304 --> 01:26:17.244
lesion called a STIC lesion. That is, as you know, is equivalent to DCIS in breast

1477
01:26:17.284 --> 01:26:21.204
cancer. And in these STICs, if you see cGAS positive micronuclei, there is a

1478
01:26:21.244 --> 01:26:23.144
ton of lymphocytes surrounding them.

1479
01:26:23.184 --> 01:26:26.554
So there's probably immune editing going on or an innate immune activation.

1480
01:26:27.424 --> 01:26:31.323
And then what happens is eventually the tumors figure a way to suppress interferon,

1481
01:26:31.724 --> 01:26:35.604
and in these advanced tumors, whenever you see cGAS positive micronuclei, you see

1482
01:26:35.684 --> 01:26:39.404
EMPP1. So what's happening is these are probably adenosine-producing

1483
01:26:39.504 --> 01:26:42.224
factories, really. Yeah. It's a great question.

1484
01:26:42.684 --> 01:26:42.854
Thank you.

1485
01:26:42.854 --> 01:26:43.184
Thank you.

1486
01:26:47.304 --> 01:26:49.903
I have a question also about cGAS/STING part.

1487
01:26:50.084 --> 01:26:50.244
Sure.

1488
01:26:50.964 --> 01:26:54.664
So when chronically treat cells with STING

1489
01:26:54.724 --> 01:26:58.684
agonist, it triggers ER stress, but also STING

1490
01:26:58.844 --> 01:26:59.504
level can be

1491
