1492
01:27:01.484 --> 01:27:01.524
Yeah.

1493
01:27:01.613 --> 01:27:05.284
And when you use cGAS inhibitor, now cause cGAS STING protein

1494
01:27:05.904 --> 01:27:09.564
upregulated and also maybe the ER stress is recovered.

1495
01:27:10.044 --> 01:27:11.104
How can you tell,

1496
01:27:12.424 --> 01:27:16.324
is it only the STING expression level is restored,

1497
01:27:16.424 --> 01:27:19.924
drives interferon responses, or is it the ER stress really

1498
01:27:20.504 --> 01:27:21.824
playing the role in?

1499
01:27:22.184 --> 01:27:25.124
Yeah, it's a good question. I think it's probably both.

1500
01:27:25.324 --> 01:27:28.523
My guess is the interferon is probably the most important.

1501
01:27:28.864 --> 01:27:32.784
So alleviating ER stress alone is not going to be enough if you're not making

1502
01:27:32.824 --> 01:27:36.544
interferon. But to test this formally, I think we would have to use one of the

1503
01:27:36.784 --> 01:27:40.184
selective separation of function mutants that Ashley's lab is

1504
01:27:40.504 --> 01:27:40.944
generating.

1505
01:27:42.124 --> 01:27:45.824
We haven't done that, but yeah. My guess is, you see a

1506
01:27:45.864 --> 01:27:49.544
switch, so you restore interferon, and you lose your stress. Yeah.

1507
01:27:49.844 --> 01:27:50.083
Thank you.

1508
01:27:50.244 --> 01:27:51.884
It's a great question. Yeah.

1509
01:27:51.924 --> 01:27:54.204
Hi. Thank you for a very nice talk.

1510
01:27:54.524 --> 01:27:54.644
Sure.

1511
01:27:54.744 --> 01:27:55.704
You've showed us that

1512
01:27:57.064 --> 01:27:59.904
chronic activation from the cGAS-STING pathway eventually leads to

1513
01:27:59.944 --> 01:28:02.644
desensitization of STING.

1514
01:28:02.944 --> 01:28:03.484
Yeah.

1515
01:28:03.514 --> 01:28:06.944
And that eventually we could leverage cGAS inhibition to

1516
01:28:07.004 --> 01:28:10.064
resensitize STING to whatever is happening in the tumor.

1517
01:28:10.104 --> 01:28:13.584
But then there's something that I fail to understand, probably due to my ignorance

1518
01:28:13.624 --> 01:28:14.243
of the pathway.

1519
01:28:14.434 --> 01:28:14.584
No. Yeah.

1520
01:28:15.184 --> 01:28:17.704
Is that if we manage to inhibit

1521
01:28:18.644 --> 01:28:20.684
cGAS and then resensitize STING

1522
01:28:22.344 --> 01:28:25.624
to whatever stimuli we plan to use to

1523
01:28:26.204 --> 01:28:29.324
