1524
01:28:29.344 --> 01:28:30.184
desensitize it again?

1525
01:28:30.244 --> 01:28:33.704
Yeah. That's a great question. So I think it's all going to be at the

1526
01:28:33.864 --> 01:28:37.024
dosing schedule. I would never

1527
01:28:38.004 --> 01:28:41.104
recommend inhibiting cGAS and then giving a STING agonist every day.

1528
01:28:41.474 --> 01:28:41.704
Yeah.

1529
01:28:41.904 --> 01:28:45.784
Because you're just basically doing what cancer micronuclei are doing

1530
01:28:45.844 --> 01:28:49.824
anyway. And STING doesn't need to be constantly

1531
01:28:49.924 --> 01:28:53.724
activated. It's not like a kinase inhibitor mode, like where you have to

1532
01:28:53.744 --> 01:28:55.364
protect your trough and all these things.

1533
01:28:56.204 --> 01:29:00.144
STING just needs to be activated in a pulsatile fashion to initiate immune

